  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Responses to water contamination in Poopo and peri-urban Cochabamba</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CENDA will continue work with communities affected by water contamination due to mining and agricultural activities around the Poop&#xF3; and Maylanco-Rocha sub-basins in Bolivia. This work promote approaches that work in harmony with the environment. The project will continue previous investigations into ecological restoration as a viable alternative solution - using plants that adapt to heavy metals to restore areas affected by contamination.  It will also provide training in the model of &quot;sembra y cosecha de agua&#x201D; - sowing and harvesting water, a technique by which communities replenish natural water supplies before extracting water.</narrative>
  </description>
